body:
Not sure if this is due to the output plugin or something else, but when having several checks in the same object it looks like only the last is available in the metric output.

Example script:

```javascript
import { check, group } from "k6";

export default function() {
  group("My group", () => {
    const testValue = false;

    check(testValue, {
      "check 1": (value) => {
        return value;
      },
      "check 2": (value) => {
        return !value;
      },
      "check 3": (value) => {
        return value;
      }
    });

    check(testValue, {
      "check 4": (value) => {
        return value;
      },
      "check 5": (value) => {
        return !value;
      },
      "check 6": (value) => {
        return value;
      }
    });
  });
};
```

Command:

```bash
/k6 run -u 1 -i 1 -out json=result.json tests/simple_test.js
```

Result:

```json
{"type":"Metric","data":{"type":"rate","contains":"default","sample":null},"metric":"checks"}
